title: Crash when compiling in `dev` profile but not `release` while doing intensive floating-point math: `_ZN4llvm16DwarfCompileUnit25createAndAddScopeChildrenEPNS_12LexicalScopeERNS_3DIEE+0x702`

labels.name: I-crash
labels.description: Issue: The compiler crashes (SIGSEGV, SIGABRT, etc). Use I-ICE instead when the compiler panics.

labels.name: A-LLVM
labels.description: Area: Code generation parts specific to LLVM. Both correctness bugs and optimization-related issues.

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I tried this code, which came from a modified version of the `numintsynth.py` script of @raphlinus' `spiro` project: https://gist.github.com/ctrlcctrlv/4007872ebc7bdac4f6c3e33051bef8d9 Don't be discouraged by the fact it is ≈5000 lines, it comes from a Python script, to wit: https://gist.github.com/ctrlcctrlv/bdcab4072a5862ef7c4e9f2a779bdbb4 I expected to see this happen: a successful compilation Instead, this happened: `rustc` crashed. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` fred@mapache:~/Workspace/spiro.rlib/integrate_spiro$ rustc --version --verbose rustc 1.66.0 (69f9c33d7 2022-12-12) binary: rustc commit-hash: 69f9c33d71c871fc16ac445211281c6e7a340943 commit-date: 2022-12-12 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.66.0 LLVM version: 15.0.2 fred@mapache:~/Workspace/spiro.rlib/integrate_spiro$ rustc +nightly --version --verbose rustc 1.68.0-nightly (1d12c3cea 2022-12-20) binary: rustc commit-hash: 1d12c3cea30b8ba4a09650a9e9c46fe9fbe25f0b commit-date: 2022-12-20 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.68.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.6 ```
